    589 ESTNL Element Summary Table for Nonlinear Elements Main Index The ESTNL is used for geometric and material nonlinear solutions, and is constructed from the Element Summary Table (EST). It contains one logical record for each element type. If the solution is geometric nonlinear, the element types listed under Summary of the ESTNL formats are completely copied to the ESTNL with the appendages added. If the solution is material nonlinear only, an element is checked for material nonlinearity by determining if its modulus of elasticity is defined as the first derivative of a stress- strain tabular function, as referenced via a MATS1 bulk data card. The construction of the ESTNL is as follows: the EST data block is read and each element is tested for possible nonlinearity. Initial screening is performed by examining entry 26 for an element within /GPTA1/ common block, which is the length of the nonlinear appendage. If word 26 is zero, the element record is copied to ESTL with no changes. If word 26 is not zero, the problem is checked if the solution is geometric nonlinear. If the solution is geometric nonlinear, the element record is copied to ESTNL with the appendage initialized. If the solution is material nonlinear, each element is checked if it is stress dependent. If it is not stress dependent, the EST is copied to ESTL. If it is stress dependent, the EST is copied to ESTNL and the appendage is added Record 1 - HEADER ESTNL Element Summary Table for Nonlinear Elements Word Name Type Description 1 NAME(2) CHAR4 Header record 3 LFACT RS Load factor or time 4 SUBCAS I For Riks’ method the subcase number 5 LAST RX For Riks’ method, the last conveyed load factor 6 NUMBL I Number of bubble elements 7 LENEST I Length of remaining words 8 TOTELM I Total number of nonlinear elements 9 NTYPES(C) I Num of nonlinear elem types = num of data recs 10 ELTYPE I Element type 11 NNASTEL I Number of Nastran elements of this type 12 NMARCEL I Number of Marc elements of this type 13 UNDEF none Not used 14 UNDEF none Not used Words 10 through 14 repeat NTYPES times Words 7 through 14 repeat until End of Record
